  "summary": "Obfuscated payload with PowerShell execution in npm package sensivity",
  "details": "The package ships a heavily obfuscated server file (server.obf.js) using hex-named identifier mangling (_0x545d11, _0x32b92e, etc.) alongside a launcher.js that requires child_process and invokes execSync('powershell...') and spawn('powershell...') at multiple call sites (lines 120, 307, 314). The combination of an opaque obfuscated bundle plus a sibling launcher that spawns PowerShell is consistent with a Windows-targeted dropper / RAT pattern rather than a legitimate library — there is no benign reason for an obfuscated npm module to drive PowerShell via execSync/spawn. The package name ('sensivity') has no documented purpose that would justify this behavior.",
